modules.description: Provides functions to parse XML documents, extract element names, attributes, and text content. Works with input streams, strings, and event-driven callbacks for parsing. Used to process configuration files, data interchange formats, and structured text in applications requiring XML support.

This module enables event-driven XML parsing, offering handlers for element events, character data, comments, and external entities, along with namespace and configuration management. It operates on strings, bytes, and an `expat_parser` type, providing metadata like line/column positions during parsing. Use cases include real-time XML data processing, validating structured documents, or integrating with systems requiring fine-grained control over XML content extraction.
